<br>
That being said, what differentiates a Mercenary from an Armsman other than our usefulness as &quot;bubble busters&quot;?  I hope it is agreed by the community that the new Light Tank role is that of a Positional Fighter that provides melee &quot;support&quot;.  It's that &quot;support&quot; that I hope to expand upon.  I envision the majority of the Dual Wield spec line to be positionals and chains.  These positionals would provide &quot;effects&quot; that are detrimental to the opponent being attacked, such as effective snares, slows, stuns, and hopefully debuffs.  I can come up with many other ideas that would add uniqueness to the Mercenary class, via the DW spec style list, given time (of course).  For example, a rear positional style that causes the opponents next attack to fumble.  I hope to receive ideas like this from the community and receive commentary from the community as to why these ideas would or would not work.<br>
<br>
For the time being however, the Mercenary is going to have to wait for the mentioned Style and RA reviews to see any changes to the class.  Kate has already said what needs to be said regarding the Mercenary and we've been told to wait for these reviews.  I'm going to be looking for new issues that I can address in a class report whenever one is asked of me, and could use plenty of feedback on this.  <br>
<br>
The issues I feel need the most attention:<br>
<br>
Flank needs a boost.  Either a To-Hit bonus, or make the Flank/Shadow's Rain chain do more damage to make up for the fact it will fail often.<br>
<br>
Charge is near useless in its current implementation for anyone other than a soloing Merc.  Even then, End Potions negate this unique ability of our class.<br>
<br>
Shield Swapping/Interface.  For those few who are Shield spec'd and want to switch from DW to S/S without dragging and dropping from inventory.<br>
<br>
Dirty Tricks.  One final tweak to add an effect that will make using DT against a non-melee an option. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#000000>(9/25/03 12:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mercenary Vision</span><hr size=1> My comments:<br>
<br>
First I mostly agree with your assessment.<br>
<br>
1) Flank improvements. While a med or high-to-hit bonus is needed for any style to be worthwhile, to me it's not something I care about when we have a poor rear-positional chain. Flank chain to me is just fluff not what I rely on in most combat situations and I don't see it changing even if they added a stun to shadow's rain. (On my 2H armsmen for a year I tried playing around with the side chain which has  higher growth rates than flank chain and a stun on 2nd style and still didn't find it effective enough to always use it). In short I'd rather see more effort in improving our rear-positional styles similar to  berserkers. Or work on improving both <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2) Regarding charge, I find it quite useful in RvR. I also carry endurance potions and they save me a ton compared to my armsmen who goes through them 3x faster because I sprint a lot. There is also a timer on potions if I recall right (i haven't tested this recently though since I have been playing my merc more). Of course any improvements to charge would be welcome. A lot of mercs find charge switching to sprint a problem, would be nice ot have a toggle option for this.<br>
<br>
3) shield swapping and DT ideas right on. DT could perhaps apply the same fumble effect on casters with their spells once it procs including if they use Mastery of Concentration. Shield users can do this with a stun so this would be a special form for the merc to acheive a similar but lesser result (high chance to distract vs a 9second stun).<br>
<br>
4) There maybe an issue with Evade I for mercs not scaling up with dex/qui buffs (with or maybe if the merc doesn't have dodger levels). This has been reported before in other tests by a number of people but I was never able to confirm if fact or fiction. I did run some tests some time ago and couldn't see a difference but my sample was not large enough to be confident of my results. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=danyan@lighttanksofdaoc>Danyan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#000000>(9/25/03 1:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mercenary Vision</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>shield swapping and DT ideas right on. DT could perhaps apply the same fumble effect on casters with their spells once it procs including if they use Mastery of Concentration. Shield users can do this with a stun so this would be a special form for the merc to acheive a similar but lesser result (high chance to distract vs a 9second stun).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
