I don't think adding even more ways to fail casts is what casters need right now, in particular, I don't think us being able to interrupt a 24 point 30-minute timer RA with our free 7-minute timer ability is a good plan. MOC is already the most expensive ability in the game (24 points buys you 15s every 30 mins), it doesn't need nerfing to the point of uselessness. The difference with a shield stun is that the caster can purge the shield stun and is then immune for 1 minute so cannot be reinterrupted with a shield. Dirty tricks can be reprocced easily and has no immunity.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure what a suitable proc for dirty tricks is that affects caters but not tanks - perhaps a dex debuff or casting speed debuff of some sort. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary TL</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#000000>(9/25/03 2:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mercenary Vision</span><hr size=1> I've had one suggestion of adding a Nearsight effect to Dirty Tricks (makes some sense, right?).  It won't stop the caster from going to town on you if you just land a hit as you run by, but it will prevent the caster from nuking your clerics or support if they're far enough away.<br>
