<br>
Now as a merc I'd LOVE to have such an ability, but I don't think that kind of power is really needed for the mercenary to be effective. the trouble is a small like 15% nearsight has no real noticable effect and a high effect is overpowering. If we want omething to harm casters I would think a medium sized acuity debuff or small power drain over time ( something like 5-8 power a tick, which equates to one less cast of a 33 power nuke or half a spread heal) or something of that nature, which hinders their ability to do dmg to a small degree but doesn't cripple their primary str ( range). I could make roleplay explainations about the distractions and such but its all tripe anyway since Mythic could make bull explainations for mercs growing wings and flying if they were so inclined.<br>
<br>
Also I'd ask it be looked into ifT CAUSES fumbles or simply makes natural misses into fumbles more often. I get the impression its the latter and personally think that the effect is not significant enough Vs a high wpn skill melee ( who seldom miss). I have no logs of this or anything but its something  to look into at some point.<br>
<br>
Also on Flank+ shadows rain its been shown the + to hit for rvr has such little bearing so as to be neglible and thus any change to it would be a pve orientated one. Thus I don't think its really a problem, although on the other hand I wouldn't turn down a + to hit bonus on it either since I remember pve being quite the suck before dual shadows~<br>
<br>
As for a style change I wouldn't mind some kind of positional chain/non-reactionary stun. Eclipse/penumbra/shadows rain all prime candidates for change in the future and possibly removing slash styles from hotbar altogether ( damn you back slash~)<br>
<br>
Anyway I'm a relatively content fotm reroll~ a little boost to DT to make it have some effect on my primary targets and I'd be happy as a pig in...mud.<br>
