<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1) Styles:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> From Blademaster TL report(blue) feedback(red)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Role of the Light Tanks – The concern of the ability of the light tank to play the role of an &quot;assist tank&quot; in PvP combat is still a major issue. Most of this relates to the inability to control player aggression (versus mob aggression) - there is also the issue of &quot;fun factor&quot; in this role, as the vision of this class has seemingly changed from the original vision, which many who play the class still currently hold. One suggestion to help in this role would be to allow Light Tanks to use reactionaries based on the main tank's reactions (parries, evades) to the target.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">This is a good suggestion and one of many things we're looking into. Don't expect anything on this for 1.65, however.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
