<br>
Evade:  It's nice to think that evade isn't scaling or being affected by stats, but I'd like to have a bit more solid ground to stand on if I bring it up.  I guess what I'm asking for are ideas on HOW to test something like this.  I'll do the testing myself, or ask some people I know might help... but as it is, there's no method to test it to my knowledge.<br>
<br>
Dirty Tricks:  Ideas for enhancing this ability are flying around and I'm liking that.  So far:<br>
<br>
-Nearsight<br>
-Stacking Self Haste while DT is active<br>
-Reduction in style endurance cost while DT is active<br>
-Acuity stat debuff<br>
<br>
Parry Skill:  A reason to spec into it, or spec high into it with benefits similar to shield spec.  It's already been mentioned in TL reports and Mythic is entertaining the idea as far as I know.  I'm all for this as well.<br>
<br>
Ok, on to styles.  This is a DRAFT!  This is not what I intend to add into the next TL report.  Everyone knows there's a Style Review on the way sometime, and I want to be ready to plead my case to take the opportunity to revamp DW.  The Style and RA reviews, as well as the ToA expansion, will be the only chances to get improvements to the Mercenary class in the near future.<br>
<br>
General Philosophy:<br>
<br>
  Front Positionals and follow up chains (defensive nature)<br>
    -Low End costs<br>
    -Detaunt<br>
    -Defensive Bonuses<br>
    -Attack speed debuff (slows)<br>
    -Keep Dual Shadows as is (lvl 50 style).<br>
<br>
  Rear Positionals and follow up chains (utility styles)<br>
    -High End costs<br>
    -Taunt<br>
    -Defensive Penalties<br>
    -Snares/Roots, Cause Fumble<br>
<br>
  Side Positional and follow up chains (Offensive nature)<br>
    -Medium End costs<br>
    -High Damage (high growth rates)<br>
    -Procs, Stat Debuffs<br>
<br>
  Parry Reactionary and follow up chains<br>
    -Basically keeping Reflection/Hypnotic Darkness as is.<br>
    -Stuns<br>
   <br>
  Evade Reactionary and follow up chains<br>
    -Highest damage (rarest form of defense)<br>
    -Bleed?<br>
<br>
  Openers all have High End costs and To-Hit bonuses.<br>
  Follow up chains have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>lower</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> End costs and the big payoffs.<br>
<br>
Styles:<br>
<br>
2-   Beginner Style, Anytime<br>
4-   Side Positional<br>
8-   Front Positional, Detaunt<br>
10- Evade Reactionary<br>
12- Rear Positional, Taunt<br>
15- Target is Blocked (TIB) Reactionary<br>
18- Parry Reactionary (Reflection)<br>
21- Target is Parried (TIP) Reactionary<br>
25- Front followup<br>
29- Rear followup<br>
34- Parry followup (Hypnotic Darkness)<br>
39- Evade followup<br>
44- Side followup<br>
50- Front Positional (Dual Shadows)<br>
<br>
Reasoning:  <br>
<br>
1) All Mercs will have access to a second style list to draw from for utilitary styles.<br>
2) Infiltrators share the DW spec line with Mercenaries, so I tried to have the potentially powerful stuff late in the spec.<br>
<br>
Basically, when you hit lvl 5 and are allowed to spec into DW, you have the potential to get the lvl 2 and lvl 4 style.  That gives you an anytime style for low level PvE and the first taste of the &quot;positional fighter&quot; philosophy with an offensive side positional.<br>
<br>
By lvl 8, after using the offensive side positional and drawing aggro all the time, the Merc will be all too ready for a defensive (detaunt) style, which is conveniently on a front positional (wouldn't make sense on any other positional).<br>
<br>
At lvl 10, Mercenaries get Evade I, and if they spec 10 in DW, they'll have the opportunity to use their Evade Reactionary (once in a blue moon).<br>
<br>
At lvl 12 they round out their positional arsenal and begin using styles that help a group with CC type effects and Taunt.<br>
<br>
By lvl 15, both Armsmen and Paladins are using large shields and Reavers get large shields at lvl 17.  All 3 could be using guard by this level.  Being able to use a reactionary based off these classes ability to block would be a nice addition to the class.<br>
<br>
At lvl 18, Mercenaries can take advantage of the Parry ability they received at lvl 17.  They have another reactionary in their arsenal.<br>
<br>
At lvl 21, they improve on their lvl 18 ability by being able to use a reactionary based on groupmates parrying.<br>
<br>
At lvl 25, the Mercenary begins to learn how to chain their styles.  The followup to the front positional allows them to slow their opponents which gives groupmates a chance to draw aggro.<br>
<br>
At lvl 29, the Mercenary learns to chain a rear positional style which Snares the opponent in the event that Taunt doesn't succeed.<br>
<br>
At lvl 34, more chains, and a stun.<br>
<br>
At lvl 39, yet more chains, big damage..watch out for that uber Merc Evade!<br>
<br>
At lvl 44? Yup, more chains.  Best place for a Merc to be, is the side!<br>
<br>
Finally, lvl 50.  Just the &quot;I'm spec'd 50 DW, think ya can take me head on!?&quot; style.<br>
<br>
Bah, too long!  Don't be too brutal when you pick this apart..  :P <p>Kerrec Snowmane<br>
Mercenary Team Lead<br>
R6L2, Palomides.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#000000>(9/25/03 3:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mercenary Vision</span><hr size=1> &quot;You get stunned, which interrupts your cast. If you purge then subsequent hits do not interrupt for the duration of MOC.&quot;<br>
<br>
I was not aware that MOC kept going for the duration after interruption. Thanks for setting me straight on this.<br>
